A former Cabinet member dismissed by Governor Ferdinand Waititu has challenged the decision in court. John Mugwe (pictured), who was in charge of Water, Environment and Natural Resources docket, has instituted a suit in the Employment and Labour Relations Court in Nairobi. ALSO READ:

Kiambu to have only 500 bars, Waititu declares Last week, Waititu sacked Mugwe after sending him on a 30-day compulsory leave. Mugwe was the Roads, Transport and Infrastructure minister before he changed dockets. The governor accused him of incompetence and not being a good team player. Waititu has said he will nominate Karungo Thangw’a as Mugwe’s replacement.  The court set an inter-party hearing for this morning.